{"page": "Skyrim:Souls", "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"notice-default vmid\" style=\"background-color:#EEEEFF;border-color:#AAAAFF;text-align:center;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width:100%\"><b>This page or section is incomplete.  You can help by adding to it.</b><br />This page is in progress. Some creatures and information about them are missing. If you have some information about creatures, please help us by editing this page.<br /><span style=\"font-size: 90%;\">For more information, see the <a href=\"/wiki/Help:Contents\" title=\"Help:Contents\">help files</a>, the <a href=\"/wiki/UESPWiki:Style_Guide\" title=\"UESPWiki:Style Guide\">style guide</a>, and this article's <span class=\"plainlinks\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.uesp.net/wiki/Skyrim_talk:Souls\">talk page</a></span>.</span></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div style=\"font-style: italic; padding-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">\n<p>This article is about the souls in soul gems.&#32;&#32;For the NPCs in the Soul Cairn, see <a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Soul\" title=\"Skyrim:Soul\">Soul</a>.\n</p>\n</div>\n<p>Every <b><a href=\"/wiki/Lore:Souls\" title=\"Lore:Souls\">soul</a></b> in Skyrim is one of six possible strengths: <a href=\"/wiki/Category:Skyrim-Souls-Petty\" title=\"Category:Skyrim-Souls-Petty\">Petty</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Category:Skyrim-Souls-Lesser\" title=\"Category:Skyrim-Souls-Lesser\">Lesser</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Category:Skyrim-Souls-Common\" title=\"Category:Skyrim-Souls-Common\">Common</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Category:Skyrim-Souls-Greater\" title=\"Category:Skyrim-Souls-Greater\">Greater</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Category:Skyrim-Souls-Grand\" title=\"Category:Skyrim-Souls-Grand\">Grand</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/Category:Skyrim-Souls-Black\" title=\"Category:Skyrim-Souls-Black\">Black</a>. More powerful creatures have more powerful souls. When a creature or NPC dies under a <a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Soul_Trap_(effect)\" title=\"Skyrim:Soul Trap (effect)\">Soul Trap</a> effect, its soul is captured in the smallest sufficiently-sized <a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Soul_Gems\" title=\"Skyrim:Soul Gems\">soul gem</a> in the player's inventory. A soul may fill a gem larger than itself, which may be undesirable if one is in short supply of large gems. Filled soul gems may be used for <a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Enchanting\" title=\"Skyrim:Enchanting\">enchanting</a> items and <a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Enchanting#Recharging_Weapons\" title=\"Skyrim:Enchanting\">recharging weapons</a>.\n</p><p>All NPCs, <a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Dremora\" title=\"Skyrim:Dremora\">Dremora</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Ghost\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Skyrim:Ghost\">ghosts</a> have Black souls, which are as powerful as Grand souls but only fit in Black soul gems or <a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:The_Black_Star_(item)\" title=\"Skyrim:The Black Star (item)\">The Black Star</a>. The soul level of any other creature is instead determined by its level as listed below; most creatures have a static level, but certain \"leveled\" creatures have a level equal to the player's level, possibly with a modifier (i.e. a multiplier or offset) applied.\n</p>\n<table class=\"wikitable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>Soul Level</th>\n<th>Charge Capacity</th>\n<th>Creature Level\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><b>Petty</b></td>\n<td>250</td>\n<td>1-3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><b>Lesser</b></td>\n<td>500</td>\n<td>4-15\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><b>Common</b></td>\n<td>1000</td>\n<td>16-27\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><b>Greater</b></td>\n<td>2000</td>\n<td>28-37\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><b>Grand</b></td>\n<td>3000</td>\n<td>38+ or <a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:NPCs\" title=\"Skyrim:NPCs\">NPC</a>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Souls_Table\">Souls Table</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Skyrim:Souls&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Souls Table\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>This table lists the soul levels of creatures in Skyrim, though not NPCs (all of them have Black souls). Leveled creatures have any level modifiers listed in superscript.  For \"special\" leveled creatures, see that creature's page.\n</p>\n<table class=\"wikitable sortable striped\" style=\"margin:0 auto\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>Creature\n</th>\n<th>Soul Level\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Alpha_Wolf\" title=\"Skyrim:Alpha Wolf\">Alpha Wolf</a></td>\n<td>Petty\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Ash_Hopper\" title=\"Skyrim:Ash Hopper\">Ash Hopper</a><sup style=\"line-height:1.0\"><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Dragonborn\" title=\"Skyrim:Dragonborn\">DB</a></sup></td>\n<td>Lesser\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Ash_Spawn\" title=\"Skyrim:Ash Spawn\">Ash Spawn</a><sup style=\"line-height:1.0\"><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Dragonborn\" title=\"Skyrim:Dragonborn\">DB</a></sup></td>\n<td>Common\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Ash_Spawn_Skirmisher\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Skyrim:Ash Spawn Skirmisher\">Ash Spawn Skirmisher</a><sup style=\"line-height:1.0\"><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Dragonborn\" title=\"Skyrim:Dragonborn\">DB</a></sup></td>\n<td>Greater\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Ash_Spawn_Immolator\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Skyrim:Ash Spawn Immolator\">Ash Spawn Immolator</a><sup style=\"line-height:1.0\"><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Dragonborn\" title=\"Skyrim:Dragonborn\">DB</a></sup></td>\n<td>Grand\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Bear\" title=\"Skyrim:Bear\">Bear</a></td>\n<td>Lesser\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Betty_Netch\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Skyrim:Betty Netch\">Betty Netch</a><sup style=\"line-height:1.0\"><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Dragonborn\" title=\"Skyrim:Dragonborn\">DB</a></sup></td>\n<td>Grand\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Bristleback\" title=\"Skyrim:Bristleback\">Bristleback</a><sup style=\"line-height:1.0\"><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Dragonborn\" title=\"Skyrim:Dragonborn\">DB</a></sup></td>\n<td>Lesser\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Burnt_Spriggan\" title=\"Skyrim:Burnt Spriggan\">Burnt Spriggan</a><sup style=\"line-height:1.0\"><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Dragonborn\" title=\"Skyrim:Dragonborn\">DB</a></sup></td>\n<td>Greater\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Bull_Netch\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Skyrim:Bull Netch\">Bull Netch</a><sup style=\"line-height:1.0\"><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Dragonborn\" title=\"Skyrim:Dragonborn\">DB</a></sup></td>\n<td>Greater\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Cave_Bear\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Skyrim:Cave Bear\">Cave Bear</a></td>\n<td>Common\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Chaurus_Hunter\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Skyrim:Chaurus Hunter\">Chaurus Hunter</a><sup><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Dawnguard\" title=\"Skyrim:Dawnguard\">DG</a></sup></td>\n<td>Greater\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Chaurus_Reaper\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Skyrim:Chaurus Reaper\">Chaurus Reaper</a></td>\n<td>Common\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Chaurus\" title=\"Skyrim:Chaurus\">Chaurus</a></td>\n<td>Lesser\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Chicken\" title=\"Skyrim:Chicken\">Chicken</a></td>\n<td>Petty\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"2\"><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Corrupted_Shade\" title=\"Skyrim:Corrupted Shade\">Corrupted Shade</a>\n</td>\n<td>Leveled\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Petty\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Cow\" title=\"Skyrim:Cow\">Cow</a></td>\n<td>Petty\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Curalmil\" title=\"Skyrim:Curalmil\">Curalmil</a></td>\n<td>Common\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Deer\" title=\"Skyrim:Deer\">Deer</a></td>\n<td>Petty\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Death_Hound\" title=\"Skyrim:Death Hound\">Death Hound</a><sup><a href=\"/wiki/Skyrim:Dawnguard\" title=\"Skyrim:Dawnguard\">DG</a></sup></td